#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:5
msgid "Redact Values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:7
msgid ""
"The Redact Values module allows administrators to redact property values."
" Administrators will be able to choose a resource type, build a query to "
"filter the resources, select the property from which to redact text, "
"select the pattern to use for redaction, enter the replacement text, and "
"choose what lower roles will be allowed to view redacted text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:9
msgid ""
"To install Redact Values follow the instructions for Installing Modules "
"on the Modules documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:11
msgid "Adding a Redaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:13
msgid ""
"Select Redact Values from the Modules tab of the left-hand navigation. "
"Click the \"Add Redaction\" button in the upper right corner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:15
msgid ""
"![Add Redact Values button.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_add-"
"redact.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:17
msgid "When adding a redaction, you are required to provide:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:18
msgid "A **label** for your redaction;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:19
msgid "The **resource type** you would like to redact (item, item set, or media);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:20
msgid "The **property** from which to redact text; and,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:21
msgid "The **pattern** to use when redacting text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:23
msgid ""
"![Add Redact Values form including label, resource type, property, and "
"pattern.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_add.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:25
msgid ""
"If you'd like, you can also add a query to filter the resources from "
"which to redact text. You can add a query via the \"Edit\" button, which "
"will open a drawer on the right that provides options for narrowing your "
"search. Alternatively, you can use \"Advanced Edit\" to add your query "
"directly from the search results page by copying everything in your "
"browser's address bar starting with the question mark all the way to the "
"end of the search url (to the right). In either circumstance, be sure to "
"click the \"Apply\" button to add your query to the form. No query means "
"all resources of the specified resource type will be included in your "
"redaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:27
msgid ""
"![Edit query tray in add Redact Values "
"form.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_query.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:29
msgid ""
"There is also a field to include the replacement text that will appear in"
" place of the redacted values. If you leave this blank, the redacted "
"field will not be visible to roles who do not have permission to view "
"redactions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:31
msgid ""
"You also have the option to give certain role types permissions in "
"viewing redactions. Note that any user with permission to update a "
"resource can automatically view its redacted text. You can allow authors "
"or researchers by checking their respective boxes. Normally, values will "
"be redacted for authors except for resources that they own and "
"researchers unless you grant them permissions in individual redactions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:33
msgid ""
"![Add Redact Values form Author and Researcher permissions "
"checkboxes.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_roles.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:35
msgid ""
"One thing to note is that the module does not apply redactions for users "
"who have permission to update the resource. That means that values will "
"never be redacted for global administrators, supervisors, and editors. "
"Users who are not logged in will never be able to view redacted values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:37
msgid ""
"Be sure to click \"Submit\" in the upper right corner to save your "
"changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:39
msgid "Managing Redactions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:41
msgid ""
"You can manage your already created redactions from the main module "
"screen. To edit a previously added redaction, click the \"Edit\" icon "
"next to the redaction you would like to change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:43
msgid ""
"![Edit button for existing "
"redactions.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_edit.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:45
msgid "Be sure to submit the form again after you have made any changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:47
msgid ""
"You can also sort your existing redactions by date or label in ascending "
"or descending order via the \"Sort\" function in the upper right corner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:49
msgid ""
"![Sort function for list of existing "
"redactions.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_sort.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:51
msgid "Adding Patterns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:53
msgid ""
"You can customize the patterns available for redactions by selecting "
"\"Patterns\" under Redact Values in the Modules tab of the left-hand "
"navigation. To create a new pattern, select the \"Add Pattern\" button in"
" the upper right corner. You will be asked to provide both a **Label** "
"and a **Pattern**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:55
msgid ""
"![Add Pattern form for Redact Values module including Label and Pattern "
"fields.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_add-pattern.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:57
msgid ""
"For the pattern, you must enter the regular expression pattern that "
"identifies the sequence of characters that will be redacted. You must "
"enclose the pattern with "
"[delimiters](https://www.php.net/manual/en/regexp.reference.delimiters.php)."
" You may use "
"[modifiers](https://www.php.net/manual/en/reference.pcre.pattern.modifiers.php)."
" For more information on regular expressions, see [Regular-"
"Expressions.info](https://www.regular-expressions.info/) and [PCRE "
"Patterns](https://www.php.net/manual/en/pcre.pattern.php). To validate "
"your pattern, try [RegExr](https://regexr.com/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:59
msgid ""
"Once you have added this information, click \"Submit\" in the upper right"
" corner. Your added pattern should now appear in the Pattern dropdown "
"menu when adding a redaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/redactvalues.md:61
msgid ""
"![Example of new pattern added to Pattern field in add Redact Values "
"form.](../modules/modulesfiles/redactValues_pattern-dropdown.png)"
msgstr ""

